qa_question-9-question = Which Games SlimeVR Work With?
qa_question-9-answer = SlimeVR Trackers work with any VR game that supports Full-Body Tracking, including but not limited to **VRChat**, **NeosVR**, **Blade And Sorcery**, **Dance Dash**, **Zenith: Nexus**, **Chillout VR**, **Resonite**, **LIV** and many others! Any game that supports FBT via SteamVR, OSC or VMC are compatible with SlimeVR Trackers!

qa_question-10-question = Which Headsets SlimeVR is Compatible With?
qa_question-10-answer = SlimeVR Trackers work with any modern VR and XR headset that can work with SteamVR, as well as many standalone headsets, including but not limited to Valve Index, Meta Quest 1, 2, 3, Pro and others (aka Oculus Quest 1, 2, 3, Pro), Oculus Quest, HTC Vive, Vive Pro, Vajro, Bigscreen Byond, Pico 3, Pico 4, and many-many others!

qa_question-11-question = Which vTubing Software SlimeVR is Compatible With?
qa_question-11-answer = limeVR Trackers are compatible with any vTubing software that can work with OSC or VMC protocols or compatible with SteamVR, which are most of them, including VSeeFace, Warudo, Tracking Worlds and many more!

qa_question-12-question = Which Motion Capture Software SlimeVR is Compatible With?
qa_question-12-answer = SlimeVR Trackers are compatible with Motion Capture (MoCap) software that can work with OSC or VMC protocols, or with SteamVR, or that can import BVH files, including Blender, Unreal Engine and others.

